# Multi-WAN Failover

This file documents the design, configuration, troubleshooting, and validation of Multi-WAN failover in the OPNsense SOC homelab using Gateway Groups and policy-based routing.

## Objective

Simulate two independent ISP connections and configure automatic failover between WAN1 and WAN2 so that if the primary WAN goes offline, traffic seamlessly routes through the secondary WAN without manual intervention.

## Environment

| Interface | VirtualBox Adapter | Network | Gateway | Monitor IP |
|-----------|-------------------|---------|---------|------------|
| WAN (em0) | Adapter 1 | NAT Network 1 — 10.0.2.0/24 | 10.0.2.1 | 8.8.4.4 |
| LAN (em1) | Adapter 2 | Internal Network — 10.200.200.0/24 | 10.200.200.254 | — |
| WAN2 (em2) | Adapter 3 | NAT Network 2 — 10.0.3.0/24 | 10.0.3.1 | 8.8.8.8 |

